name: aliēnigenous or indigenous
description:
ethmology

aliēnigenus in latin,
1. different, foreign, alien, born in another country

indigenus in latin
indigenus (“native, born in a country”), from indi- (indu-), an old derivative of in (“in”), gen- the root of gignō (“give birth to”), and English -ous
